Class JMLCompletionTest

            • nl.utwente.jmlplugin.JMLCompletionTest
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.intellij.testFramework.TestIndexingModeSupporter, junit.framework.Test
    public class JMLCompletionTest
extends com.intellij.testFramework.fixtures.LightJavaCodeInsightFixtureTestCase
    Test for the code completion part of the plugin. The way to make the tests is by writing a java class in the completionTestData folder that has some JML for which you would like to test the completion on, then at the place that the completion should be invoked at put the "" symbol there and the test will invoke the completion there. The test will return you a list of string suggestions that the autocomplete gave, you can then check whether this was the expected list or contains the expected elements. Many tests are duplicated to check the completion with and without a semicolon as the parser has issues with incomplete expressions and like to throw error elements that completely screw up the parse tree structure where the completion is supposed to take place, this makes it a giant pain to deal with and custom handling of these circumstances is necessary, hence the tests must also test with a semicolon and without one. There is also some boiler plate that needs to be copy pasted in the test method itself, but you can look that up below.
